<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 12:18PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Oldham,
eastern Deaf Smith and southwestern Potter Counties through 100 PM
CDT...
At 1217 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Simms, or 17 miles northwest of Hereford, moving north
at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vega, Adrian, Wildorado and Simms.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
